# Example age recipient (public) keys file for backup encryption.
#
# Generate a keypair on a workstation that will *consume* the backups:
#   age-keygen -o ~/.config/casino_bot/age-identity.txt
#
# The "public key:" line printed by age-keygen (starts with "age1...")
# goes here. One recipient per line. Multiple recipients = backup can be
# decrypted by any of them (use this for ops + DR roles).
#
# Copy this file to ops/backup/age-recipients.txt and replace the line
# below with your real public keys. The file ops/backup/age-recipients.txt
# is the one read by scripts/ops/pg_backup_encrypt.sh.
#
# Public keys are SAFE to commit. Identity files (private keys) are NOT.

age1examplepublickeyplaceholderdoNOTuseinrealitymustbereplaced0000
